%% wiki

Language of Butler
==================

Words
-----

Commands
~~~~~~~~

If you want to tell your computer to do something, you need to use a command. This command is the core component of every "conversation" with your machine and can be question-line (*time?*) or a "real" command (*add â€¦*).

Primary Objects
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

There are some special objects being used in Butler's language. E. g.:

this
^^^^

Referring to the currently selected text.

you
^^^

The machine itself.

me
^^

The user (You.).

Secondary Objects
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Most commands make use of own objects like dates, locations, files, etc. These may be predifined or specified in the commands definition.
